description: Ensure UI works in light and dark themes
alwaysApply: true
---

# Theme Parity For UI Changes

- For every user-facing UI change, implement and verify both light and dark themes in the same task.
- Do not leave theme-specific regressions for follow-up fixes.
- For text, icons, and surfaces, always set explicit dark variants (`dark:*`) when colors are custom.
- For images and embedded mockups, check readability and contrast on both themes.
- During review, verify interactive states (default/hover/active/disabled) in both themes.
